  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u201c\u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u201d \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b88\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Awareness rally on \u201cPath of Health\u201d.",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The awareness rally \"On the Path of Health\" conducted by Jaffna Arogya Nagar Project started today (01) at 7 am and ended at 8 am.",
        "Jaffna. This Eruruli rally started from University Medical Faculty and from there reached Kokuvil Junction via Adiyapadam Road, from there reached Hospital Road via KKS Road and reached Vembadi Junction via Av Road.",
        "From there it reached Parameshwarach Junction via Palali Road and ended at the entrance of Jaffna University main campus.",
        "Jaffna University Vice-Chancellor C. Sirisarkunaraja, Faculty of Medicine Dean E. Surendrakumaran, Northern Province Health Services Director A. Ketheeswaran, Jaffna University Vice-Chancellor C. Sirisakunaraja, . District Government President K. Mahesan, Director of Jaffna Teaching Hospital T. Sathyamurthy, Jaffna City Chief Minister V. Manivannan, Jaffna City Commissioner E. T. Jayaseelan, and government officials, representatives of non-governmental organizations, university staff, students and school students participated in the event.",
        "This awareness rally was carried out under the project \"Jaffna Arogya Nagara\" sponsored by the World Health Organization in order to create awareness about health care among the public.",
        "In many countries around the world, the World Bank has implemented the concept of \u201cHealthy Cities\u201d and identified significant healthy cities. Based on that, Jaffna city is selected for the first time in South Asia and the project is being implemented.",
        "World Health Organization in direct coordination and implementation of Department of Community and Family Medicine, Jaffna University School of Medicine, Jaffna. It is noteworthy that various parties including Municipal Council, UNICEF, Department of Health Services, Urban Development Authority, Ministry of Education, Government and Non-Government Organizations, Jaffna District Secretariat, Jaffna and Nallur Divisional Secretariats are providing their cooperation as partners of this project."
      ],
